Package: MiCBuS
Type: Package
Title: MiCBuS: Marker Gene Mining for Unknown Cell Types Using Bulk and Single-Cell RNA-Seq Data
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Shanshan Zhang
Maintainer: Shanshan Zhang <sszhang3@arizona.edu>
Description: Tools for identifying marker genes of unknown cell types by integrating bulk RNA-seq, 
    single-cell RNA-seq, and Dirichlet-based pseudo-bulk simulation. The workflow includes building 
    a cell-type reference, detecting scRNA-seq marker genes, estimating initial proportions, 
    generating Dirichlet pseudo-bulk RNA-seq samples, and performing shrinkage-based differential 
    expression analysis to identify pseudo marker genes for unknown or unannotated cell types.
